  <data key="d14">ann.concept-injustice-contrary-to-concept-charity-st-ii-ii-q059-a004-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q059.a004.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( I-II:12:5 ), when we were treating of the distinction of sins , a mortal sin is one that is contrary to charity which gives life to the soul . Now every injury inflicted on another person is of itself contrary to charity , which moves us to will the good of another. And</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
</edge>
<edge source="concept.injustice" target="concept.justice" id="edge.concept.injustice.opposed_by.concept.justice">
