  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q060.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Judgment properly denotes the act of a judge as such. Now a judge [judex] is so called because he asserts the right [jus dicens] and right is the object of justice , as stated above ( II-II:57:1 ). Consequently the original meaning of the word "judgment" is a statement or de</data>
