  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">se when one is the prosecutor, and the other the defendant. Therefore in criminal cases the judge cannot sentence a man unless the latter has an accuser, according to Acts 25:16 : "It is not the custom of the Romans to condemn any man , before that he who is accused have his accusers present, and have liberty t</data>
