  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q060.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">es rightly about matters relating to chastity . Therefore judgment, which denotes a right decision about what is just , belongs properly to justice . For this reason the Philosopher says (Ethic. v, 4) that "men have recourse to a judge as to one who is the personification of justice ."</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
</edge>
