  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q058.a001.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that lawyers have unfittingly defined justice as being "the perpetual and constant will to render to each one his right" [Digest. i, 1; De Just. et Jure 10. For, according to the Philosopher (Ethic. v, 1), </data>
