  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that the act of justice is not to render to each one his own. For Augustine (De Trin. xiv, 9) ascribes to justice the act of succoring the needy. Now in succoring the needy we give them what is not theirs b</data>
