  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q063.a001.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that respect of persons is not a sin . For the word "person" includes a reference to personal dignity [Cf. I:29:3 ad 2 ]. Now it belongs to distributive justice to consider personal dignity. Therefore respe</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
