  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">External things can be considered in two ways. First, as regards their nature , and this is not subject to the power of man , but only to the power of God Whose mere will all things obey. Secondly, as regards their use, and in this way, man has a natural domin</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
