  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">evil , being intent on the evil itself, then evil speaking will be unlawful in both ways, and this is what is meant by cursing. On the other hand if a man commands or desires another's evil under the aspect of good , it is lawful; and it may be called cursing, not strictly speaking, bu</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q076" target="st.ii-ii.q076.a001" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q076.contains.st.ii-ii.q076.a001">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q076.contains.st.ii-ii.q076.a001</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q076</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.76 — Cursing</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q076.a001</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.76 a.1 — May one lawfully curse another?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q076.a001.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem unlawful to curse anyone. For it is unlawful to disregard the command of the Apostle in whom Christ spoke, according to 2 Corinthians 13:3 . Now he commanded ( Romans 12:14 ), "Bless and curse not." Therefo</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q076" target="st.ii-ii.q076.a002" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q076.contains.st.ii-ii.q076.a002">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q076.contains.st.ii-ii.q076.a002</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q076</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.76 — Cursing</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q076.a002</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.76 a.2 — May one lawfully curse an irrational creature?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q076.a002.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that it is unlawful to curse an irrational creature. Cursing would seem to be lawful chiefly in its relation to punishment. Now irrational creatures are not competent subjects either of guilt or of punishme</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q076" target="st.ii-ii.q076.a003" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q076.contains.st.ii-ii.q076.a003">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q076.contains.st.ii-ii.q076.a003</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q076</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.76 — Cursing</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q076.a003</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.76 a.3 — Is cursing a mortal sin?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q076.a003.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that cursing is not a mortal sin . For Augustine in a homily On the Fire of Purgatory [Serm. civ in the appendix of St. Augustine's works] reckons cursing among slight sins . But such sins are venial. There</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q076" target="st.ii-ii.q076.a004" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q076.contains.st.ii-ii.q076.a004">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q076.contains.st.ii-ii.q076.a004</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q076</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.76 — Cursing</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q076.a004</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.76 a.4 — Its comparison with other sins</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q076.a004.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that cursing is a graver sin than backbiting. Cursing would seem to be a kind of blasphemy , as implied in the canonical epistle of Jude (verse 9) where it is said that "when Michael the archangel, disputin</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q077" target="concept.cheating" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q077.treated_in.concept.cheating">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q077.treated_in.concept.cheating</data>
