  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q057-a003-treated-in-concept-right-st-ii-ii-q057-a003-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q057.a003.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( Article 2 ), the natural right or just is that which by its very nature is adjusted to or commensurate with another person . Now this may happen in two ways; first, according as it is consid</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q057.a003" target="concept.right_of_nations" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q057.a003.treated_in.concept.right_of_nations">
