  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q057.a003.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">right which we call natural , is common to us and other animals according to the first kind of commensuration. But the right of nations falls short of natural right in this sense, as the jurist [Digest. i, 1; De Just. et Jure i] says because "the latter is common to all animals, while the forme</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
