  <data key="d17">Respect of persons is opposed to distributive justice . For the equality of distributive justice consists in allotting various things to various persons in proportion to their pe</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q063.a002" target="concept.respect_of_persons" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q063.a002.treated_in.concept.respect_of_persons">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q063.a002.treated_in.concept.respect_of_persons</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q063.a002</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.63 a.2 — Does it take place in the dispensation of spiritualities?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.respect_of_persons</data>
  <data key="d12">Respect of Persons</data>
  <data key="d13">sin_type</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q063-a002-treated-in-concept-respect-of-persons-st-ii-ii-q063-a002-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q063.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( Article 1 ), respect of persons is a sin , in so far as it is contrary to justice . Now the graver the matter in which justice is transgressed, the more grievous the sin : so that, spiritual</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q063.a003" target="concept.respect_of_persons" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q063.a003.treated_in.concept.respect_of_persons">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q063.a003.treated_in.concept.respect_of_persons</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q063.a003</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.63 a.3 — Does it take place in showing honor?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.respect_of_persons</data>
  <data key="d12">Respect of Persons</data>
  <data key="d13">sin_type</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q063-a003-treated-in-concept-respect-of-persons-st-ii-ii-q063-a003-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q063.a003.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">ir occupying a higher position in the community: but if they be honored merely for their wealth , it will be the sin of respect of persons . Hence the Replies to the Objections are clear.</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q063.a004" target="concept.judgment" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q063.a004.treated_in.concept.judgment">
