  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q063.a004</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.63 a.4 — Does it take place in judicial sentences?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.judgment</data>
  <data key="d12">Judgment</data>
  <data key="d13">act_type</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q063-a004-treated-in-concept-judgment-st-ii-ii-q063-a004-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q063.a004.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( II-II:60:1 ), judgment is an act of justice , in as much as the judge restores to the equality of justice , those things which may cause an opposite inequality. Now respect of person</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q063.a004" target="concept.respect_of_persons" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q063.a004.treated_in.concept.respect_of_persons">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q063.a004.treated_in.concept.respect_of_persons</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q063.a004</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.63 a.4 — Does it take place in judicial sentences?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.respect_of_persons</data>
  <data key="d12">Respect of Persons</data>
  <data key="d13">sin_type</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q063-a004-treated-in-concept-respect-of-persons-st-ii-ii-q063-a004-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q063.a004.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">in as much as the judge restores to the equality of justice , those things which may cause an opposite inequality. Now respect of persons involves a certain inequality, in so far as something is allotted to a person out of that proportion to him in which the equality of justice consists. Wherefor</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q064.a001" target="concept.life" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q064.a001.treated_in.concept.life">
