  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q064.a003.treated_in.concept.life</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q064.a003</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.64 a.3 — Is this lawful to a private individual, or to a public person only?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.life</data>
  <data key="d12">Life</data>
  <data key="d13">domain</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q064-a003-treated-in-concept-life-st-ii-ii-q064-a003-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q064.a003.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( Article 2 ), it is lawful to kill an evildoer in so far as it is directed to the welfare of the whole community, so that it belongs to him alone who has charge of the community's welfare. Thus it belongs to a physician to cut off a decayed li</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q064.a003" target="concept.private_execution" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q064.a003.treated_in.concept.private_execution">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q064.a003.treated_in.concept.private_execution</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q064.a003</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.64 a.3 — Is this lawful to a private individual, or to a public person only?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
