  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q065.a004.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Other things being equal, an injury is a more grievous sin according as it affects more persons ; and hence it is that it is a more grievous sin to strike or injure a person in authority than a private individual , because it conduces to the injury of the whol</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
