  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q066-a003-treated-in-concept-property-st-ii-ii-q066-a003-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q066.a003.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Three things combine together to constitute theft . The first belongs to theft as being contrary to justice , which gives to each one that which is his, so that it belongs to theft to take possession of what is another's. The second thing belongs to theft as d</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
