  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q068-a002-treated-in-concept-accuser-role-st-ii-ii-q068-a002-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q068.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( II-II:67:3 ), when the process in a criminal case goes by way of accusation, the accuser is in the position of a party, so that the judge stands between the accuser and the accused for the purpose of the trial of justice , wherein it behooves one t</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
