  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q068.a003.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( Article 1 ), accusation is ordered for the common good which it aims at procuring by means of knowledge of the crime. Now no man ought to injure a person unjustly , in order to promote the common good . Wherefore a man may sin in two ways whe</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
