  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q069.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Whoever acts against the due order of justice , sins mortally, as stated above ( II-II:59:4 ). Now it belongs to the order of justice that a man should obey his superior in those matters to which the rights of his authority extend. Again, the judge, as stated</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
