  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q069.a003.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">There are two motives for which a man appeals. First through confidence in the justice of his cause , seeing that he is unjustly oppressed by the judge, and then it is lawful for him to appeal, because this is a prudent means of escape. Hence it is laid down (</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
