  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q070-a003-treated-in-concept-witness-role-st-ii-ii-q070-a003-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q070.a003.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( Article 2 ), the authority of evidence is not infallible but probable; and consequently the evidence for one side is weakened by whatever strengthens the probability of the other. Now the reliability of a person's evidence is weakened, someti</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q070.a004" target="concept.false_witness" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q070.a004.treated_in.concept.false_witness">
