  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q070-a004-treated-in-concept-false-witness-st-ii-ii-q070-a004-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q070.a004.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">idence by the precept of the decalogue is expressed in this form when it is said ( Exodus 20:16 ), "Thou shalt not bear false witness against thy neighbor." For one does nothing against a man by preventing him from doing someone an injury, but only by taking away his justice . Thirdly, owing</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q070.a004" target="concept.witness_role" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q070.a004.treated_in.concept.witness_role">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q070.a004.treated_in.concept.witness_role</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q070.a004</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.70 a.4 — Is it a mortal sin to bear false witness?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.witness_role</data>
  <data key="d12">Witness</data>
  <data key="d13">role</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q070-a004-treated-in-concept-witness-role-st-ii-ii-q070-a004-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q070.a004.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">False evidence has a threefold deformity. The first is owing to perjury, since witnesses are admitted only on oath and on this count it is always a mortal sin . Secondly, owing to the violation of justice , and on this account it is a mortal sin</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q071.a001" target="concept.advocate_role" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q071.a001.treated_in.concept.advocate_role">
