  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q071.a003.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">at do" it. Hence it was stated above ( II-II:62:07 ), that all such are bound to restitution. Now it is evident that an advocate provides both assistance and counsel to the party for whom he pleads. Wherefore, if knowingly he defends an unjust cause , without doubt he sins grievously, an</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q071.a003" target="concept.dishonest_advocacy" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q071.a003.treated_in.concept.dishonest_advocacy">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q071.a003.treated_in.concept.dishonest_advocacy</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q071.a003</data>
