  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">A man may justly receive payment for granting what he is not bound to grant. Now it is evident that an advocate is not always bound to consent to plead, or to give advice in other people's causes . Wherefore, if he sell his pleading or advice, he does not act</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
