  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q072-a001-treated-in-concept-honor-st-ii-ii-q072-a001-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q072.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Reviling denotes the dishonoring of a person , and this happens in two ways: for since honor results from excellence, one person dishonors another, first, by depriving him of the excellence</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
