  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q074.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">ighbor which are likely to defame him, or at least to depreciate his good name : whereas a tale-bearer intends to sever friendship, as appears from the gloss quoted above and from the saying of Proverbs 26:20 , "Where the tale-bearer is taken away, contentions shall cease." Hence it is tha</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
