  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q079.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">n general, it belongs to every virtue to do good and to avoid evil : and in this sense they cannot be reckoned parts of justice , except justice be taken in the sense of "all virtue " [Cf. II-II:58:5 ]. And yet even if justice be taken in this sense it regards a certain special aspect o</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
