  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q079.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">The term transgression is derived from bodily movement and applied to moral actions. Now a person is said to transgress in bodily movement, when he steps [graditur] beyond [trans] a</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
