  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q079.a004.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">ry black is not-white, but not conversely. Now it is evident that transgression is contrary to an act of virtue , while omission denotes the negation thereof: for instance it is a sin of omission , if one fail to give one's parents due reverence, while it is a sin of transgression to rev</data>
